	     Polokwane – The body of a man was found in on the R81 road in Limpopo on Tuesday, with multiple stab wounds to his head and the area below his left ear. Police spokesperson Constable Mamabolo Monatse said community members alerted police to the body. Monatse said preliminary investigation revealed that the man, in his late forties, might have been killed somewhere else and dumped on the side of the road.  He is yet to be identified. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  